{"id": "EUVD-2022-55771", "enisaUuid": "5923b078-689b-30ac-896d-b9a545579cdf", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/amdgpu: fix pci device refcount leak\n\nAs comment of pci_get_domain_bus_and_slot() says, it returns\na pci device with refcount increment, when finish using it,\nthe caller must decrement the reference count by calling\npci_dev_put().\n\nSo before returning from amdgpu_device_resume|suspend_display_audio(),\npci_dev_put() is called to avoid refcount leak.", "datePublished": "2025-12-24T15:30:32", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-24T15:30:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3725a8f26bdbc38dfdf545836117f1e069277c91", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/02105f0b3021ee5853b2fa50853c42f35fc01cfd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f13661b72a61708cecb06562f8acff068a4f31f7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d7352b410471cbebf6350b2990bae82bb0d59a76", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b85e285e3d6352b02947fc1b72303673dfacb0aa", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50718"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50718"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00931d14-cbe6-3fa0-a1d0-1b7c3dde60dd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.16"}, {"id": "0df5f73e-c256-3bb3-9bea-62f6cb48b9c2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3f12acc8d6d4b2e62fab8f652d7075a859d80b42 <3725a8f26bdbc38dfdf545836117f1e069277c91"}, {"id": "193e3b65-9f30-3d3b-a209-7185e99ebfb4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.2"}, {"id": "3dcd3f57-ea98-3375-8d3a-2af12ca9fe2d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3f12acc8d6d4b2e62fab8f652d7075a859d80b42 <d7352b410471cbebf6350b2990bae82bb0d59a76"}, {"id": "494dc630-fe02-30eb-9568-40933b12d714", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.86"}, {"id": "552d9531-e668-33c2-9660-8022349cb3f7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "64b5cd32-52e7-35